{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 Calibri;}{\f1 Courier New;}}\paperw11907\paperh16840\margl1440\margr1440\margt1080\margb1080\fs22 Toolbox Calculator\line \line Assignment Information\line Dar es Salaam Institute of Technology\line Civil Engineering Department\line Module: Programming Fundamentals for Technicians (GST 05117)\line Class: OD24CE-2 | Assignment Type: Group | Assignment No: 3\line Group Number: 11 | Submission Date: March 1, 2026\line \line Group Members\line 1. ABDULAZIZ MAHYORO (240121429579)\line 2. LAWRENCE MMATAMBWE (220121417491)\line 3. ELIAH HANGO (240121476067)\line 4. HUSSEIN OMARY (240121449049)\line 5. ROBERT JAMES (240121479897)\line 6. GIDEON OLANG'U (240121429421)\line 7. MOSES MFUSE (24012317533)\line 8. GLORIA DAUDI (240121453512)\line \line Brief Explanation (One-Page Summary)\line This mini project was prepared by Group 11 to practice core C programming skills in a direct and practical way. The main goal is to let a user enter data, process that data logically, and get a clear output report.\line In this project (Toolbox Calculator), menu-driven calculator implementing add, subtract, multiply, and divide operations.\line \line How the Program Works\line 1. It shows a clear prompt/menu to the user.\line 2. It accepts and validates user input to avoid wrong values.\line 3. It processes data using conditions, loops, and calculations.\line 4. It prints final results in a readable format.\line \line Concepts Practiced\line - Switch statements\line - Arithmetic operators\line - Conditionals\line - Input/Output\line - Error handling (division by zero)\line \line Sample Output (short example)\line === Toolbox Calculator ===\line 1. Add\line 2. Subtract\line 3. Multiply\line 4. Divide\line 5. Exit\line Choose an option: 4\line Enter two numbers: 12 0\line \line Presentation Note\line This mini project is intentionally simple, focused, and easy to explain during presentation.}